result.execSummary:
The defendant April Beatrice Frazier was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. April Beatrice Frazier is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • April Beatrice Frazier was found guilty of Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: as a Party to a Crime, Penalties for Felonies-Class "F" Felony], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Court addresses the victime.  Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights.  Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea.  Court reads charge and maximum penalty.  DE pleads Guilty to Ct 1 in 15CF262 & Ct. 2 15CF395.  Guilty pleas are entered.  Court reviews the police reports attached to the Criminal Complaints.  Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE guilty of Ct 1 in 15CF262 & Ct. 2 in 15CF395.  On motion of the State, Crt dismisses Ct 2 in 15CF262 & Ct. 1 in 15CF395. Sentencing arguments. Ct. 1 in 15CF262 and to run concurrent with Ct. 2 15CF395

Preliminary hearing on June 22, 2015 at 03:30 pm.

It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, Emily J., her residence/place of employment or Shawntell H.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, through the mail, and/or through a third person.  The aforementioned condition of bond/bail is set pursuant to Sec. 969.02(3)(d), Wis Stats.

Further, it is ORDERED that if the defendant fails to comply with the conditions of his/her bond/bail that he/she may be charged with the offense of bailjumping contrary to Sec. 946.49(1)(a), Wis. Stats.
